Absolutely—here’s a small, safe style layer that keeps the visual tone steady and readable while meeting accessibility contrast requirements.  
Everything uses static colours; no motion or flashing.

```css
/* --- Hotline buttons --- */
.hotline-btn {
  display: inline-block;
  margin: 8px 12px 0 0;
  padding: 14px 20px;
  font-family: "Inter", "Noto Sans", Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: #ffffff;                    /* High contrast text */
  background-color: #00706F;         /* Teal-green accent */
  border-radius: 6px;
  border: 2px solid #005654;         /* Slightly darker outline */
  min-width: 200px;
}

/* Keyboard-focus outline — clearly visible */
.hotline-btn:focus {
  outline: 3px solid #ffc107;        /* Warm amber for visibility */
  outline-offset: 3px;
}

/* High-contrast hover (no animation, no opacity fade) */
.hotline-btn:hover,
.hotline-btn:active {
  background-color: #005654;
  color: #ffffff;
}

/* --- General page background for calm contrast --- */
body {
  background-color: #F2EFEA;         /* Warm matte beige-gray */
  color: #222222;                    /* Charcoal text */
  line-height: 1.6;
  font-size: 16px;
  padding: 20px;
}

/* Optional dark/focus mode */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  body {
    background-color: #2C2C2C;
    color: #E8E6E3;
  }
  .hotline-btn {
    background-color: #A9D6C2;
    color: #2C2C2C;
    border-color: #7BB397;
  }
  .hotline-btn:focus {
    outline: 3px solid #fff176;      /* Bright but stable yellow */
  }
}
```

### Design notes
* Colours pass **WCAG AA** contrast ratios.  
* No movement effects; hover states change colour instantly with no transitions.  
* Large padding and rounded corners make touch‑targets comfortable on mobile.  
* Focus outline guarantees keyboard and screen‑reader users can easily identify active elements.  
* Optional dark mode automatically follows user system settings.

